🎃CANDY PUMPKIN PATCH🎃 This was a very quick setup with a roll of paper and dot marker (regular marker could work to make the dots as well). 👉 Our bag of pumpkin candies has been lots of fun for Fall sensory play! This pumpkin patch matchup activity is SO much fun and excellent fine motor work 👌 Simply make dots in rows to create the “patch” and send our pumpkin candies for your little to match to each dot. •••• let me know in comments today if you’ll try this at home and share with a momma friend! 🎃🥰👇 

.
.
.
.

node.text:
COOKING WITH KIDS @tovlajr 👩🏽‍🍳🧑🏻‍🍳❤️ad|  I’ve always tried to include my little ones when cooking or baking because they’re naturally drawn to it — but also because I know the many benefits for them when helping in the kitchen! My 4 year year old for example is always trying to new veggies when he helps me prepare and chop them for dinner! Kids that help with cooking and food prep are more likely to try new foods. In addition, they are learning important life skills, developing their fine motor muscles and learning early math skills in measurement. 🥣•••• The @tovlajr Complete Cooking & Baking Set for kids has everything a little one needs to safely join you, having fun and building independence in the kitchen. My boys couldn’t have been happier about having their own special kitchen tools & utensils to use alongside me. ❤️👉👉👉👉👉 You can use the link in my bio today to take you to the Tovla Jr. site and my discount code is already applied. OR visit Tovlajr.com and use code LITTLEONESLEARN10 for a discount today 🥰 Share this amazingggg (unique) kids gift idea with someone in comments today & leave a comment if you include your kids in the kitchen!👇
.
